The evidence with the title 'Bhopal - Wikipedia ' says Bhopal is the capital city of the Indian state of Madhya Pradesh and the administrative headquarters of Bhopal district and Bhopal division . The city was the capital of the former Bhopal State .  ... An alternative theory says that the city is named after another king called Bhupala  ... . Diwali and Eid are major festivals in Bhopal . 
